#To configure VPN for linux, follow these steps:

#Download Anyconnect-linux package from this link. 
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1UMsHQf_4VwjzRXe-6funrFRl22UZKbzX/view

#Extract the file using command 

tar xvf anyconnect-linux64-4.9.00086.tgz

cd anyconnect-linux64-4.9.00086/vpn/

sh vpn_install.sh -y

#Now you can open vpn using command /opt/cisco/anyconnect/bin/vpnui 

#Or simply go to applications and select cisco anyconnect vpn.

#Run this command on terminal: 

sudo apt-get install openconnect network-manager-openconnect network-manager-openconnect-gnome

#Go to settings on your Linux and inside Network, add VPN option.

#Select Anyconnect. And on the gateway, Enter this link ‘anyconnect.anydomain.com’ and click okay.
